SYSTEM: ESP32 + PCA9685 + 4 Servos + 2 Joysticks + External Servo Power

==============================
ESP32 ↔ PCA9685 (I2C)
==============================
ESP32 3.3V  → PCA9685 VCC
ESP32 GND   → PCA9685 GND
ESP32 GPIO21 (SDA) → PCA9685 SDA
ESP32 GPIO22 (SCL) → PCA9685 SCL

==============================
EXTERNAL SERVO POWER
==============================
External +5V / +6V → PCA9685 V+
External GND       → PCA9685 GND
(External GND MUST be common with ESP32 GND)

==============================
SERVO CONNECTIONS (PCA9685)
==============================
Servo Wire Color:
Brown/Black → GND
Red         → V+
Yellow      → Signal

Servo A (Base)          → PCA9685 Channel 0
Servo B (Shoulder Left)→ PCA9685 Channel 1
Servo C (Shoulder Right, Mirrored) → PCA9685 Channel 2
Servo D (Gripper)       → PCA9685 Channel 3

(Channel pin order on PCA9685: Signal / V+ / GND)

==============================
JOYSTICK MODULE 1 (Base + Shoulder)
==============================
Joystick VCC → ESP32 3.3V
Joystick GND → ESP32 GND
Joystick VRx → ESP32 GPIO34  (Base rotation)
Joystick VRy → ESP32 GPIO35  (Shoulder up/down)
Joystick SW  → ESP32 GPIO25  (Optional button)

==============================
JOYSTICK MODULE 2 (Gripper + Spare)
==============================
Joystick VCC → ESP32 3.3V
Joystick GND → ESP32 GND
Joystick VRx → ESP32 GPIO32  (Gripper open/close)
Joystick VRy → ESP32 GPIO33  (Spare / wrist)
Joystick SW  → ESP32 GPIO26  (Optional button)

==============================
CRITICAL RULES
==============================
• NEVER power servos from ESP32
• Joysticks must use 3.3V only
• Use ADC1 pins only (GPIO 32–39)
• ALL grounds must be common
• PCA9685 I2C address = 0x40 (A0–A5 jumpers OPEN)
